      <acqinfo id="aspace_6a6e7bf1cf28035a40dffc794f61420f">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The papers were the gifts of William T. Peters, son-in-law of Ithiel Town, 1858, and of the Collector's Shop, New Haven, Connecticut, 1939. The negatives for the photostatic copies were loaned by C. W. Whittlesey in 1941.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_51cda8cbf7defa50cdc2e2f54fd49bdd">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
